# Godot UAV Simulator - Cursor Rules (Draft)

## Scope

These rules apply to all coding tasks in this repository.

## 1) Documentation Sync Is Mandatory

After **any code change**, always review and update:

- `README.md`
- `ARCHITECTURE.md`

Also update these when relevant:

- `docs/RUN_MODES.md` (if execution paths, CLI flags, or run behavior changes)
- `docs/EXPERIMENT_TEMPLATE.md` (if experiment structure/process changes)

## 2) Required Post-Change Checklist

Before finishing a coding task, the agent must confirm:

- [ ] Code changes are complete
- [ ] `README.md` reviewed and updated
- [ ] `ARCHITECTURE.md` reviewed and updated
- [ ] `docs/RUN_MODES.md` reviewed/updated if run modes changed
- [ ] `docs/EXPERIMENT_TEMPLATE.md` reviewed/updated if experiment workflow changed
- [ ] Documentation "Last Updated" fields adjusted where applicable
- [ ] Documentation reflects actual implementation and paths

## 3) Reporting Format Required in Final Response

When code is changed, the final response must include:

1. Files modified
2. Documentation files reviewed
3. Documentation files updated
4. Short explanation of why each doc update was needed (or why no update was needed)

## 4) Run-Mode Consistency Rule

Do not introduce undocumented run behavior.

If adding/changing execution behavior, ensure consistency across:
- `README.md`
- `ARCHITECTURE.md`
- `docs/RUN_MODES.md`

## 5) Experiment Organization Rule

New experiments must follow the `Experiments/ExN-*` pattern and align with `docs/EXPERIMENT_TEMPLATE.md`.
Do not mix experiment-only orchestration logic into core runtime modules unless explicitly requested.

## 6) Safety / Hygiene

- Do not revert unrelated user changes.
- Do not use destructive git commands unless explicitly requested.
- Prefer minimal, targeted edits.
- Keep docs and code aligned in the same task; do not defer doc updates.